To add a new node to your Kafka cluster, you need to upgrade your installation by providing some parameters to the *helm upgrade* command:

* Use the *--replicaCount* flag to modify the number of nodes in your Kafka deployment.

The following will be an example to add more nodes:

~~~
$ helm upgrade my-release <%= variable :repo_name, :platform %>/kafka \
--set replicaCount=NUMBER_OF_REPLICAS
~~~
